Description: Three joining fragments of rim and body of East Greek pottery eye cup; interior glazed with one added red band lined in white; exterior: eye, arching eyebrow and part of nose; two verticals to right and two bands below handle zone.
Curator's comments: From the same vessel as GR1886.4-1.1039.
Bibliographic references: Möller 2000 / Naukratis, Trade in Archaic Greece (p. 256, no. 4)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.466)
